com.camerontec.util.datatypes

Class IntegerArrayList

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.util.datatypes.IntegerArrayList
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IntegerList, IntegerListView, List, ListView, Printable, Recyclable

    public class IntegerArrayList
extends Object
implements IntegerList
    An implementation of IntegerList backed by an int array.

    This list has the following characteristics:

    • Gets are fast.
    • Adds are fast if there is sufficient capacity.
    • Removing the first or last element is fast.
    • Clearing the list is fast - the underlying data is left intact.
    • The remove and insert operations take advantage of available capacity as much as possible in order to reduce garbage creation and minimize iterations over the underlying array.
    • When the underlying array must be grown, the new capacity will be at least double the current size.
